Used on discussion forums on the internet in relation to the posting of new forum messages on old threads, with the intent  of either ressurecting an old topic thread or the poster's personal amusement.

While some topics may merit re-visiting, this is generally unproductive to discussions
that may have moved on. Many forums have set rules that forbid this practice, although
it sometimes is permitted if the contribution is relevant or useful.

Posting a comment on a thread discussing the theatrical premiere of Star Wars, for instance, would
be considered old news. Commenting on new dvd releases, however relevant, may be more useful in a topic more suited for the comment, or creating a new thread on the forum.